<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1606">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/290.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to
                                    Chile</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Minister of Foreign Affairs informs me that negotiations have been
                            resumed with Peru through intermediation of Chilean Consul at Callao and
                            has shown to me telegrams exchanged recently by which the effect of
                            secret message of the President of Peru to the Peruvian Congress which
                            caused interruption of negotiations is neutralized. From telegrams both
                            parties appear anxious to reach satisfactory arrangement but no definite
                            propositions have been advanced. Minister of Foreign Affairs hopes to
                            settle on basis outlined in my despatch No. 300.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>